erature, unveiling how introspection in Second Temple Judaism both parallels and differs from forms of introspective selfhood in Greco‑Roman cultures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aSelfxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh1 aCollins, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262964423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300262964/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles